SIMPLE: implicitly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Implicitly
<hw>Im*plic"it*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In
an implicit manner; without reserve; with unreserved
confidence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not to dispute the methods of his providence, but humbly and
<qex>implicitly</qex> to acquiesce in and adore them.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By implication; impliedly; <as>as, to deny the
providence of God is <ex>implicitly</ex> to deny his
existence</as>.</def> <rj><au>Bentley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Implicitness</ent>⟦br⟧
